==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stab culture
<hw>Stab culture</hw>. <fld>(Bacteriol.)</fld> <def>A culture made by
inoculating a solid medium, as gelatin, with the puncture of a needle or
wire; -- called also <altname>stab</altname>. The growths are usually of
characteristic form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stabiliment</ent>⟦br⟧
